  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to Social Protection Programme 2, Emergency Response Fund - Scale Up of Cabo Delgado Emergency Response, Including Influx of Needs for Arrivals from Palma</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As a result of insecurity in Cabo Delgado, the humanitarian situation is deteriorating in both hosting and displaced communities, and for those left behind. As the number of internally displaced persons (IDPs) continues to increase and new displacement sites are being established in areas that were not previously covered, a further expansion in humanitarian capacity and presence on the ground is critical to prevent a further deterioration of the humanitarian situation. The objective of the project is to scale up and expand the emergency, life-saving support to address the immediate and emerging needs of internally displaced persons and other affected communities in northern Mozambique, including those affected by the crisis in Palma. The response focuses on four areas: Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM), camp coordination and camp management, integrated mental health and psychosocial support and protection, and shelter/non-food items.</narrative>
  </description>
